summary: This is an FBI Electronic Surveillance (ELSUR) evidence envelope form documenting the transfer of intercepted materials, likely from a Title III wiretap or consensual monitoring. It indicates the materials were transferred for permanent storage on January 17, 2000, and contains administrative custody signatures.

events.title: Evidence transferred for permanent storage
events.description: Magnetic tape or computer disk containing intercepted communications was transferred to permanent FBI storage.

keyFacts: This is an FBI ELSUR (Electronic Surveillance) evidence envelope form.
The intercepted materials (magnetic tape/computer disk) were transferred for permanent storage on January 17, 2000.
The form indicates the interception was either court-authorized (Title III) or consensual monitoring.
The form contains multiple custody signatures documenting the chain of evidence.
No specific individuals, locations, or case details are revealed in this administrative cover sheet.
